      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUNSETS (2) is a city class galloper struggling to win in much tougher races lately. Will find this far easier and gets chance to find some form. Best figures CHASING APHRODITE (1) resumed in town then came home soundly when fourth in the Stony Creek Cup. Aided by the claim and ready to win after two runs back. Hard to beat. SOUND OF JURA (5) was a winner in much easier grade two back then carried 63.5kg last time at Swan Hill. This much tougher but plummets in the weights. Should be winding up strongly. FOX APPEAL (3) is an honest type overdue for a win, placing last three. Drawn for a soft run and should be in the mix. STAR BUYER (4) won only try course and distance and should go close again.",
